This paper discusses an extension of the XGBoost algorithm for regression tasks, which is a popular machine learning algorithm used in various fields such as computer vision, natural language processing, and data science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also includes experiments on synthetic and real-world datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
